Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government and the Mozambique National 
Resistance [Renamo] had already selected 2,622 soldiers to join 
the future Mozambique Defense Armed Forces by 18 March. Of this 
number, 1,893 come from the government army, while the remaining 
729 came from Renamo. The UN Operations in Mozambique daily 
report points out that by 18 March the government had 
demobilized 2,721 soldiers, while Renamo had demobilized 100 
men. Radio Mozambique in Tete Province points out that 250 
government soldiers were demobilized at the Xitima assembly area 
in Cahora Bassa District today. 

